&gt; &gt; little)  &gt;  &gt; so here is my real world use case: openQRM is 
&gt; a platform 
&gt; &gt; for  &gt; provisioning and managing services in a DC. a service is an 
&gt; &gt; entity  &gt; named VirtualEnvironment that encapsulates both a set of 
&gt; &gt; policies on  &gt; how to provision and manage the real service and a 
&gt; &gt; capture of the  &gt; real service&#39;s state (resources, 
