&gt; primary ones 
&gt; &gt; are to  &gt; start and stop it. starting means resources are selected 
&gt; &gt; from a pool  &gt; and assigned to work for the service, the 
&gt; software is 
&gt; &gt; deployed on  &gt; them and the service is monitored. stopping is the 
&gt; &gt; reverse.
&gt; &gt;  &gt; obviously openQRM does all this. the client just 
&gt; requests to &#39;start&#39;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; or &#39;stop&#39;.
&gt; &gt;  &gt;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; now, it is hard for me to see &#39;start&#39; and &#39;stop&#39; as 
&gt; values of the  
&gt; &gt; &gt; &#39;currentactivity&#39; property. if anything, it looks like a 
&gt; masquerade  
&gt; &gt; &gt; of the RPC equivalent of posting to the 
&gt; VirtualEnvironment entity  &gt; 
&gt; &gt; with the pair &#39;action=start&#39; .
&gt; &gt;  &gt;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; thank you for your help,
