&gt; &gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; POST /BuildingManager
&gt; &gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Content-Type: application/ blueprint &lt;-- this type is  &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; fictous; it would need to be standardized within the realm 
&gt; of  &gt; your 
&gt; &gt; system  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;blueprint&gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;wall 
&gt; location=&quot;.. ..&quot;/&gt;  
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &lt;/blueprint&gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; IOW, in a RESTful 
&gt; &gt; system clients late-bind to resources based on  &gt; &gt; 
&gt; runtime-declared 
&gt; &gt; abstract bahavior of those resources and they  &gt; &gt; 
&gt; communicate via a 
